   helpful air current. When it's needed, my breath weapon is pure bolts of Lightning. How's that for a neat piece of carry-on
                              luggage? See you amongst the clouds!<br><br> </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uheartsongsteelsoul.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Heartsong Steelsoul</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/25/02 8:20:20 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23458.topic&index=6>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Poll - EQ 2 Equipment Decay</span><hr size=1> I'd say Yes on equipment decay <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/utalzarbbh.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Talzar BBH</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/25/02 8:32:03 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23458.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Poll - EQ 2 Equipment Decay</span><hr size=1> That is the main reason I quit DAoC.  Playing as a paladin which I loved do you know what I spent maybe a 1/4 of my online time doing?  Finding a smith with high enough skill to repair my armor.  <br>
<br>
If you played Albion you know that paladins are the kings of holding aggro.  If you didnt play it they are kind of like EQ bards but their chants (songs) really piss mobs off.  <br>
<br>
I would have to repair my VERY expensive to begin with armor twice a week.  That may not sound like a lot but what it boiled down to was me having to drop whatever I was doing when one of five smiths logged on so I could dash to Camelot to get my armor repaired while they were there.<br>
<br>
Item decay doesnt have to be a bad thing.  If done correctly it can make a great economy.  DAoC was on the right track but in my opinion it went well beyond time consuming and into the realm of just a waste of my time.  <br>
<br>
I really doubt EQ2 will get it right.  I will be happy if I am wrong though. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/utalzarbbh.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Talzar BBH</A> at: 4/25/02 8:32:47 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ualisdahre.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Alisdahre</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/25/02 8:32:19 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23458.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Poll - EQ 2 Equipment Decay</span><hr size=1> It's a completely different game.  That one will have decay, while EQ1 does not.  It's a design decision, and people decide if they want to play the game introduced or not.<br>
<br>
Frankly, I hate it that everyone and his brother complained continously about this and that roleplaying feature in our current EQ and got the game to be &quot;completely changed&quot; from the game that I originally bought.  Today's EQ is not the EQ that first came out.  I'm not talking about upgrades and tweaks... I'm talking about fundamental, direction defining roleplay features that were changed.<br>
<br>
Please... don't steal another good roleplaying game from the people that enjoy that sort of game.  There &quot;used&quot; to be a good in-character roleplaying game that I played once... unfortunately everyone bitched enough to have that game completely changed into the non-roleplaying game that we have today.  Please don't destroy this new game that is coming out as well.  Some of us will buy it for a reason, and it's crappy that the reasons we buy it are stamped out by everyone else who really wanted a &quot;different style&quot; of game.<br>
<br>
If I want a football game, I'm not going to go out and buy a soccer game and bitch until the developers make it more resemble football.  All of the people that wanted to play soccer will be disappointed, because their game has just been stolen from them.  They bought soccer because &quot;that's what was advertised&quot; and that's what they want to play.  If you don't want to play a soccer game that's fine, don't buy it.  But don't come in and change the game that people &quot;thought&quot; they were getting, leaving them &quot;without a game&quot;.<br>
<br>
Mind you, I love Everquest in it's current configuration.  But I loved the old Everquest &quot;more&quot;.  I was a roleplayer.  Everyone bitching about this and that stole that game from me.  I no longer have a roleplaying game to play.  I no longer have the roleplaying game that I bought.  It's completely different.  Don't change this new game that's coming out.  Some of us like it's features and might buy it because of them.  What's the point of going for those features if you all are just going to beat them out of the design?  Buy a game that suits your tastes... don't steal one that suits my tastes from me by changing it to your tastes.  Those are not my tastes, hence the reason I bought the game that suited my tastes in the beginning.<br>
<br>
Roleplayers want roleplaying games, hardcore gamers want what they want.  It's completely unfair that the hardcore gamers play their hardcore games, the come into the roleplayers games and completely screw it up and change it into a hardcore game AS WELL.  Will there EVER be a roleplaying game?  Not if the hardcore gamers keep stealing them.  Play your games, we'll play ours.  Please don't taint ours, leaving us stuck playing out-of-character hard-core games.  While I find them fun as well, if I'm in a mood to roleplay, I want the freedom to play my roleplaying game.  Unfortunately, every online roleplaying game I've played has been killed by non-roleplaying gamers time and time again.  Everytime I start one, it's cool... but then soon after the game doesn't exist anymore because non-roleplayers screw it up.  Is it too much to ask for a roleplaying game to be created that REMAINS a roleplaying game?<br>
<br>
